Overview
Focused on Amazon S3 storage service: creating buckets, uploading/downloading files, and handling permissions.

## Practice
- Created a new bucket with a unique name.  
- Uploaded a small file to the bucket.  
- Downloaded the same file to verify access.  
- Tested access without permissions → got "Access Denied".  
- Fixed by attaching the correct IAM policy.  

## Permissions
- Learned the difference between IAM Policy (controls user actions) and Bucket Policy (controls bucket access).  
- Understood why "Access Denied" happens and how to solve it.  

## Lessons Learned
- How to create and manage S3 buckets.  
- Importance of unique bucket names.  
- Difference between IAM and Bucket Policies.  
- Common troubleshooting steps for S3 errors.  

